Two men were shot by a lone gunman outside of a Manhattan public housing complex on Tuesday night, police sources said. The victims were attacked in front of the Fulton Houses in Chelsea at the corner of West 19th Street and Ninth Avenue at about 10 p.m., sources said. One of the men was struck in the torso and was hospitalized in critical condition. The other victim was shot in the right arm. His injuries were not considered life threatening. The gunman on West 19th Street towards 10th Avenue. No arrests were immediately made.